modules.description: This module handles low-level memory allocation using page-aligned blocks, primarily working with `Bigarray.Array1.t` and `Cstruct.t` for efficient buffer manipulation. It provides functions to allocate, convert, and manage memory pages, including direct memory copying and address inspection. Concrete use cases include managing memory for I/O operations, handling page-aligned buffers for system calls, and interfacing with C libraries requiring direct memory access.
